{"cursor":"13836","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":" in 1848]]\n\nA 'refracting' or 'refractor telescope' is a type of optical telescope that uses\na lens as its objective to form an image (also referred to a dioptric\ntelescope). The refracting telescope design was originally used in spy glasses\nand astronomical telescopes but is also used for long focus camera lenses.\nAlthough large refracting telescopes were very popular in the second half of the\n19th century, for most research purposes the refracting telescope has been\nsuperseded by the reflecting telescope.\n","linknr":327,"url":"Refracting_telescope","recorded":1362574442,"links":63,"instances":["optics","optics","geometry","optics","optics","optics","optics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Telescopes","Telescope types"],"headings":["Invention","Refracting telescope designs","Technical considerations","Notable refracting telescopes","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Refractor_Cincinnati_observatory.jpg/220px-Refractor_Cincinnati_observatory.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Kepschem.png/400px-Kepschem.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Galileantelescope.png/400px-Galileantelescope.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Telescope_140_foot_Johann_Hevelius.jpg/220px-Telescope_140_foot_Johann_Hevelius.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21w